# Releasing {{ .Manifest.Name }}

This generated CLI already includes release scaffolding for native binaries, checksums, and an install script.

## What gets published

- Darwin binaries for `amd64` and `arm64`
- Linux binaries for `amd64` and `arm64`
- `checksums.txt`
- GitHub release assets built from `.goreleaser.yaml`
- `scripts/install.sh` for one-line installs
- `scripts/install-skills.sh` for installing generated skills with the `skills` CLI
{{- if .Release.HasHomebrewTap }}
- Homebrew formula updates pushed to `{{ .Release.HomebrewTap }}`
{{- end }}

## First-time setup

1. Put this generated project in its own GitHub repository.
{{- if .Release.HasRepo }}
   Expected repository: `{{ .Release.Repo }}`.
{{- else }}
   If you want the install script to work without extra env vars, regenerate with `--repo owner/name` or set `REPO=owner/name` when running `scripts/install.sh`.
{{- end }}
2. Create a tag like `v0.1.0` and push it.
3. GitHub Actions runs `.github/workflows/release.yml`.
{{- if .Release.HasHomebrewTap }}
4. Add a `HOMEBREW_TAP_GITHUB_TOKEN` repository secret with push access to `{{ .Release.HomebrewTap }}`.
{{- end }}

## Local release

```bash
go install github.com/goreleaser/goreleaser/v2@latest
goreleaser release --clean
```

## Install paths for users

Direct install script:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{{ if .Release.HasRepo }}{{ .Release.Repo }}{{ else }}OWNER/REPO{{ end }}/main/scripts/install.sh | sh
```

Install the primary bootstrap skill for the agent:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{{ if .Release.HasRepo }}{{ .Release.Repo }}{{ else }}OWNER/REPO{{ end }}/main/scripts/install-skills.sh | sh
```

That installs the generated install skill by default. To install every generated skill at once:

```bash
INSTALL_ALL_SKILLS=1 curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{{ if .Release.HasRepo }}{{ .Release.Repo }}{{ else }}OWNER/REPO{{ end }}/main/scripts/install-skills.sh | sh
```
{{- if .Release.HasHomebrewTap }}

Homebrew:

```bash
brew install {{ .Release.HomebrewTap }}/{{ .Manifest.Name }}
```
{{- end }}
